text: The 2018 Tasmanian state election was held on 3 March 2018 to elect all 25 members of the Tasmanian House of Assembly. It was conducted by the Tasmanian Electoral Commission (TEC). The incumbent Liberal government, led by Premier Will Hodgman, won a second term in government. They were opposed by the Labor Party, led by Rebecca White. ==References== Category:2018 elections in Australia Category:Elections in Tasmania Category:2010s in Tasmania
title: 2018 Tasmanian state election
